Class BrentHashMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractHashMap<K,V>
      • BrentHashMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - key type of entries.
    V - value type of entries.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<K,V>
    public class BrentHashMap<K,V>
extends AbstractHashMap<K,V>
    This class simulates a hash map that uses Brent's method when a collision occured. Collisions help to count the frequency of keys in hash map.

      • bucketPut

        protected V bucketPut​(K key,
                      V value)
        Puts new entry to hash map. If given key is found, increases its count(frequency) number. If it is a new key and the calculated index is empty, places new entry to empty place. If it is a new key and the calculated index is not empty, it calculates new index by using Brent's method.
        Specified by:
        bucketPut in class AbstractHashMap<K,V>
